1.   DEFINITIONS
     "License" means this document.
     "Program" means the source code, object code, and associated files
     distributed under this License.
     "You" means an individual or legal entity using the Program.
     "Derivative Work" means any modification of the Program or work
     based on the Program.
     "Qualifying Entity" means a commercial entity (or group of
     affiliated entities under common control) that meets at least one
     of the following criteria, measured as of the most recently
     completed fiscal year at the time of measurement:
          a) 500 or more employees, counting full-time, part-time
             (pro-rated by full-time-equivalent), and long-term
             contractors engaged for more than 6 continuous months; or
          b) annual revenue exceeding 100 million USD, meaning the
             entity's (and its affiliates', on a consolidated basis)
             gross revenue for that fiscal year, converted to USD at
             the exchange rate prevailing on the last day of that
             fiscal year if earned in another currency.
     Once an entity meets either criterion, it is a Qualifying Entity
     for the remainder of its use of the Program, even if its employee
     count or revenue later falls back below the threshold. This status
     is not reassessed downward; Section 4.4 separately preserves an
     entity's pre-existing projects from before it first met either
     criterion.
     "Commercial Use" means any use of the Program that is intended
     for or results in commercial advantage or monetary compensation,
     including but not limited to:
          a) incorporating the Program into products or services sold
             to third parties;
          b) using the Program to provide paid services;
          c) selling copies of the Program;
          d) using the Program for internal business operations of an
             entity whose primary business activity is the sale of
             goods or services to third parties (as opposed to, e.g.,
             a non-profit, research institute, or educational body
             whose primary activity is not such sale).
     "Licensor" means the original copyright holder(s) of the Program.
     Where more than one person or entity holds the original copyright,
     any one of them may independently exercise any discretionary power
     granted to "the Licensor" under this License (e.g. Sections 3.4,
     4.5, 4.6, 7.2(c)), and a recipient who reasonably relies on such an
     exercise is not required to seek confirmation from the others.
     Allocating rights and disputes among multiple original copyright
     holders is a matter between them and does not affect this License
     as applied to recipients.

