          otherwise.
     3.5. Any party distributing the Program without including a copy
          of this License is solely responsible for any consequences
          arising from such distribution.

4.   QUALIFYING ENTITY RESTRICTIONS
     4.1. Qualifying Entities must obtain explicit written permission
          from the Licensor before engaging in Commercial Use of the
          Program.
     4.2. Non-commercial use by Qualifying Entities (research, education,
          internal testing) does not require permission.
     4.3. Use of the Program by individuals employed by Qualifying
          Entities in personal, non-work-related projects does not
          require permission.
     4.4. If an entity was not a Qualifying Entity at the time it first
          used the Program but later becomes one, it may continue using
          the Program in projects initiated before attaining Qualifying
          Entity status without additional permission. New projects
          initiated after attaining Qualifying Entity status require
          permission under Section 4.1. For this Section, a "project"
          is a distinct product, service, or codebase in which the
          Program was incorporated before the status change; continued
          development, bug fixes, and version upgrades of that same
          product or service are part of the same project, but
          incorporating the Program into a separate, newly-created
          product or service is a new project.
     4.5. Permission is considered granted if the Licensor responds to
          a request in writing (including email) and explicitly permits
          use. Silence or failure to respond does not constitute
          permission.
     4.6. The Licensor may request, sent by both email and registered
          mail with proof of delivery, that an entity provide documented
          evidence of its status (employee count or financial records).
          The 30-day period below runs from whichever of the two
          deliveries is confirmed later. If the entity fails to provide
          such evidence within 30 days of that confirmed delivery, it
          shall be conclusively presumed to be a Qualifying Entity for
          the purposes of this License, and the Licensor may pursue any
          remedies available under this License or applicable law. This
          presumption shall not apply if the entity proves that neither
          notice was actually received due to circumstances beyond its
          reasonable control.
     4.7. The Licensor bears the burden of proving that an entity
          qualifies as a Qualifying Entity under Section 1 in any legal
          dispute, unless the entity has failed to respond under
          Section 4.6.

